\series medium
(orthonormal eigenvector basis)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There exists an orthonormal eigenvector basis 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(u_{i}\right)_{i\in\left\{ 1,\ldots,n\right\} }$
\end_inset

, that means with the eigenvalues 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{i}\in\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\left\langle u_{i},u_{j}\right\rangle  & =\delta_{ij} & Au_{i} & =\lambda_{i}u_{i}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

In infinite dimensions the generalization is the 
\emph on
spectral theorem
\emph default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
First reformulate the result from linear algebra:
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Let 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{\lambda_{i}}$
\end_inset

 be the orthogonal projection operator on the eigenspace corresponding to
 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{i}$
\end_inset

.
 If this eigenspace is one dimensional, this means:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
E_{\lambda_{i}}v & =u_{i}\left\langle u_{i},v\right\rangle =\left|u_{i}\right>\left<u_{i}|v\right>
\end{align*}

\end_inset

Then one can write 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 as:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
A & =\sum_{i=1}^{n}\lambda_{i}E_{\lambda_{i}}
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Theorem 
\series medium
(spectral theorem)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $A\in L\left(H\right)$
\end_inset

 be a self-adjoint (
\lang ngerman
selbstadjungiert
\lang english
) operator, then it holds:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
A & =\int_{\sigma\left(A\right)}\lambda\dd E_{\lambda}
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\sigma\left(A\right)\subseteq\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

 is the spectrum of 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{\lambda}$
\end_inset

 the projection-valued measure (
\lang ngerman
Spektralmaß
\lang english
).
\end_layout

