\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{D}\left(\overline{A}\right)$
\end_inset

.
 Is 
\begin_inset Formula $v$
\end_inset

 unique?
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Suppose 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(u,v\right)\in\overline{\text{graph}A}$
\end_inset

.
 Then there exists a sequence 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(u_{n},v_{n}\right)\in\text{graph}\left(A\right)$
\end_inset

, with 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(u_{n},v_{n}\right)\to\left(u,v\right)$
\end_inset

.
 Equivalently:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\fall_{n\in\mathbb{N}}\ \exs_{u_{n}\in\mathcal{D}\left(A\right)}: & \left(u_{n}\to u\right)\wedge\left(Au_{n}\to v\right)
\end{align*}

\end_inset

Then we set 
\begin_inset Formula $\overline{A}u:=v$
\end_inset

.
