\end{align*}

\end_inset

Kato's condition is:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\norm{Vu}_{L^{2}}^{2} & \le a^{2}\norm u^{2}+b^{2}\norm{\Delta u}^{2}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

With
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\frac{1}{p}+\frac{1}{q} & =1
\end{align*}

\end_inset

holds:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\norm{Vu}_{L^{2}}^{2} & ?\int_{\mathbb{R}^{3}}\abs{V\left(x\right)}^{2}\abs{u\left(x\right)}^{2}\dd^{3}x\le\norm V_{2q}\cdot\underbrace{\norm u_{2p}}_{\text{Sobolev inequality}}\le\\
 & \le\norm V_{2q}\left(\varepsilon\norm{\Delta u}^{2}+c\left(\varepsilon\right)\norm u^{2}\right)
\end{align*}

\end_inset

Now holds 
\begin_inset Formula $b:=\varepsilon\norm V_{2q}^{2}<1$
\end_inset

 for sufficiently small 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon$
\end_inset

, provided that 
\begin_inset Formula $\norm V_{L^{2q}}<\infty$
\end_inset

.
 This is satisfied for the Yukawa potential, but for the Coulomb potential
 one must work a bit harder.
